CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 24, 1959, pg. 7 reads: "UNCF Workers - Among the education conscious Pittsburghers who work diligently with the United Negro College Fund are these well-known residents; The Rev. Ramsey Bridges, minister at Warren Methodist Episcopal Church; James M. Burgette, executive secretary, Centre Avenue Branch YMCA; Mrs. Clarence Pennywell Jr., publicity chairman, Fashionettes, and W.P. Young, personnel department, Lockhart Iron and Steel Co. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, left to right;  Rev. Ramsey Bridges, James M. Burgette, Mrs. Clarence Pennywell Jr., and W.P. Young, standing in interior of the Greene Hearth restaurant
